ResultStatus.Comment: When competition is stopped, usued at pre-defined points
When the unit is over but not yet unofficial or official
Results of the competition released as soon as the event is over, not waiting any official decision of the International Federation. The correctness of data must be assured
Results of the competition released as soon as the event is officially confirmed taking into account the resolution of the protests, etc.
Incomplete list, Final Ranking. Used in PDF
After the competition is no longer LIVE and a protest has been lodged

ScheduleStatus.Comment: Competition unit was schedule and will not now take place
Competition has not started and start is late (no new time)
All play is complete in the unit
Start of competition is iminent, athletes usually on FOP
Competition has started but is now stopped temporarily.
Competition has stopped and will take place at a new time (to be determined)
The start (or re-start) of the competition has changed to a new time (new time is known)
Planned break in competition (e.g. end of period)
A possible unit to be scheduled, not displayed (e.g. swim-off)
